TopicTitle: Game crashes upon launching a new campaign

Articles.Content:
OS: Windows 10
CPU: Intel i7-1265U (1.80 GHz)
GPU: Intel Iris Xe
RAM: 16 GB

Bought through Steam. Steam file validation passes.

I have KSP1 installed on the same device.

The content of two player.log files can be found at the bottom of this post.

 

Context
I bought KSP2 today. I fired it up, and started a new campaign. After having created a new campaign, during the loading screen the game either:

  • Crashes and shuts down to desktop
  • Crashes and bluescreens my device

I have only tried exploration mode so far.

Specific steps taken

  1. Create new campaign. Result: game crashes to desktop at "Loading Universe State"
  2. Try again without changes. Result: game crashes to desktop at "Loading Universe State"
  3. Create new campaign after lowering graphics settings (after consulting this forum post). Result: blue screen at "Loading Universe State"
  4. Try again without changes. Result: game crashes to desktop at "Loading Universe State"
  5. Create new campaign after deleting folder "\AppData\LocalLow\Intercept Games\Kerbal Space Program 2" according to bug-posting guidelines. Result: blue screen at "Creating Vessel"
  6. Try again without changes. Result: blue screen at "Loading Universe State"

Observations

  • Whatever happens during Loading Universe State is very likely to fail (5 crashes out of 6 attempts)
  • Changing graphics settings correlates to a blue screen in this trial
  • After deleting "\AppData\LocalLow\Intercept Games\Kerbal Space Program 2" the only observed crash was of blue-screen type

Questions

  1. Is this either known expected behaviour or a known problem, given similar computer specs?
  2. Is the cause known for this situation?
  3. Is there a solution or workaround for this problem?

 

I hope to have provided enough information in this way. Let me know if any more is needed.

Any help is very welcome!

 

Requested files

My "\AppData\LocalLow\Intercept Games\Kerbal Space Program 2\Saves" folder is empty
